Zimbabwe Inflation Below 4% by End of Year, Reuters Reports

-- B y   G o r d o n   B e l l
-- 
2011-10-19T14:04:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-19/zimbabwe-inflation-below-4-by-end-of-year-reuters-reports.html
Zimbabwe ’s inflation rate will
probably decline to below 4 percent by the end of the year,
Reuters said, citing Finance Minister  Tendai Biti .  The southern African nation planned to start a sovereign
wealth fund in 2012 to help conserve its mineral wealth, the
 news agency  cited Biti as saying.  Zimbabwe’s inflation accelerated to 4.3 percent in
September.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
